<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Ask Aer for the list of names..i am sure she wrote them done<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If Aereona has a list of names written down, and has issues or if they talked to her in anyway that was disrespectful, she can contact me. But if people were harassing you, your last post would have been the perfect time to give me those names.<br>
<br>
I don't see what Nellen has to do with any of this. He's not on my guild, as you know, and I have never met the person. If he did something crappy, like leave you all to get your own corpses, that stinks. Still has nothing to do with me.<br>
<br>
You and Medika where in the Plane of Innovation at the time, so you don't even have first hand knowledge of what Thrakkul and Perelik where saying to Skrag when they asked for a corpse summoning in Permafrost.<br>
<br>
For someone that wants to be left out of this, you sure are keeping it alive. Not once have I attacked you, or accused you of anything or your guild. I'm only responding to your posts. <br>
<br>
You ask me to leave you out of it in game, and I do. I haven't sent you a single tell since you said leave me out. But you sent me more tells, even one asking if I had sent anything, because you were zoning and might have missed it. Generally, when someone wants to be left out of something, they also stop talking it about it, they don't ask people to repeat anything they think they might have missed or post on the same subject 2 days later.<br>
<br>
Added:<br>
I talked to Aereona today, in the morning, to find out about this list of hers. Well, she did recieve some tells asking why she was trying to raid the same time I was raiding, but that none of them were harassing her or threatening her guild. And that she replied to them and said that they had rescheduled their plans. <br>
<br>
She also didn't write down any names. I do know that I have now talked to everyone in House Valiant and everyone says they the same, they never spoke to anyone in your guid. I've never known anyone in my guild to go behind my back, or not follow any request made of them.<br>
<br>
I do know that many of the people that signed up for the raid knew about the conflict of interest from the posts on the site, as I did not go around telling anyone that was not in my guild about it. I was asked about whether it was still a go by them. <br>
<br>
So, with no list, and Aereona's own words that she wasn't harassed or threatened, just asked why they were planning to raid the same time as my raid, I think saying that I sent people to harass your guild is a distortion of the turth.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, you came here, and made your posts, speaking for you guild and started this. If anyone gave people the impression that your guild was trying to fource it's will on others, to the point where people started sending your guild leader tells, asking why, it was you. Not your guild, but you.<br>
